---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const title = "Rubik's Cube Beginner Solution Algorithms";
const description = "Flip, flop, flubbedubbedop!";
const permalink = Astro.site!.href; // FIXME: using ! for now
---

<BaseLayout
  title={title}
  description={description}
  permalink={permalink}
  current="home"
>
  <section>
    <h2>Step 1: White Cross</h2>
    <p>
      Manually position the white edge pieces to form a cross on the white face.
      Match the side colors to the adjacent centers.
    </p>
    <code>R' U' R U R'</code>
    <p>(Optional helper for fixing edge positions)</p>

    <h2>Step 2: White Corners</h2>
    <p>
      Insert the white corners one by one by aligning the cubie below its target
      position and using:
    </p>
    <code>F D F'</code>
    <code>R' D' R</code>
    <code>R' D R F D2 F'</code>
    <p>To fix orientation or bump a corner down first:</p>
    <code>R' D R F D F'</code>

    <h2>Step 3: Second Layer Edges</h2>
    <p>
      Find edge pieces in the top layer without yellow. Match their front color
      with a center and move left or right:
    </p>
    <code>U R U' R' U' F' U F</code>
    <p>(For moving to the right)</p>
    <code>U' L' U L U F U' F'</code>
    <p>(For moving to the left)</p>

    <h2>Step 4: Yellow Cross</h2>
    <p>Depending on the yellow shape, use:</p>
    <code>F U R U' R' F'</code>
    <p>(For “L” shape in top-left)</p>
    <code>F R U R' U' F'</code>
    <p>(For horizontal line)</p>

    <h2>Step 5: Yellow Edges</h2>
    <p>Align yellow edge pieces with their side center colors using:</p>
    <code>U R U R' U R U2 R'</code>
    <p>(Do twice if wrong edges are opposite)</p>

    <h2>Step 6: Corner Positioning</h2>
    <p>Put at least one correct corner in the FRU position, then:</p>
    <code>U R U' L' U R' U' L</code>
    <p>Repeat until all yellow corners are in the correct positions.</p>

    <h2>Step 7: Corner Orientation</h2>
    <p>With an incorrect corner in FRU, use:</p>
    <code>(R' D' R D) (R' D' R D)</code>
    <p>If yellow is on the right</p>
    <code>(R' D' R D) × 4</code>
    <p>If yellow is on the front</p>
    <p>
      Use U or U' to rotate next incorrect corner into FRU, repeat until solved.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
